latestIgtvVideos.title: SBSE (Sapola Board of Sec Education) announces Insta Preboards for All
latestIgtvVideos.caption: The thing is, as much as I agree people with a platform must speak up in times od crisis, you gotta understand not everybody would know about everything going on in the world. I do speak up on a lot of issues but I can’t possibly have an informed opinion on everything. I’m not any smarter than the rest of you. Don’t look up to me for what is not my expertise. I may be misinformed at times. Just as much as you. If you really want someone to look up to, there are far more knowledgable and learned researchers, historians, lawyers, activists you can follow for a sound opinion. Entertainers se tum journalism expect karte ho aur wahan news channels pe journalists humare hisse ka entertainment karke nikal jaate hain. How about you hold the right people accountable for the right things? Also, I have a platform but guess what, you have a social circle too. You have an influence too. You’re just as much a voice as me. Before you tell me how to use my workplace (yes, Instagram is literally my workplace )  I wanna know how you use your workplaces to spread awareness. Do you know about every issue? Are you bringing up global issues to discuss during your office concalls? Are you asking your teachers and professors to talk about relevant issues in your virtual classes? Are you doing YOUR bit? Are you talking to your parents & neighbours  everyday about these issues? (Because guess what, most of these people aren’t on Instagram). Or is your concern for the world limited only to reminding others how to be responsible?

latestPosts.caption:
This one’s for all those times I’ve had to pick my self confidence up from the ground. Each and every time over and again. Because of failures, judgements, fate. This one’s for an entire childhood spent hiding - feeling invisible, inadequate, ugly, uncool. I walked the Cannes red carpet last night as India’s first male beauty creator. I wish I could take with me the 8 year old Ankush who used to dread going to school because everyone teased him, bullied him for the way he looked, called him a frog because his eyes were too big for his face, arms too scrawny, interests not masculine enough & show him how much love he could get for just simply being his true self. I wish he could see he’s worth being celebrated. Here’s to each one of you who continue to find that one reason to hang in there when there are 99 to give up. I see you, and one day the world will too ❤️
.
Thank you @brut.india for this opportunity, I couldn’t be more grateful!
.

latestPosts.caption:
Xmas with a very questionable playlist 😆
.
1.5 years in Mumbai, and I’m realising I’ve lived here like it’s a long work trip. Haven’t allowed myself a single day without an agenda. Haven’t made enough friends, haven’t watched enough sunsets , haven’t made enough memories. So, here’s me trying to change that. I’m gonna call this phase ‘building a life in Mumbai’. Merry xmas everyone! I hope we all start living a little more. #merrychristmas
